<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="8.[474,1113,1390,1451]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
KEY TO THE SPECIES OF 
<taxonomicName authority="FROM" authorityName="FROM" box="[818,1113,1390,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,1113,1390,1416]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">PARAMISOLAMPIDIUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
FROM 
<collectingCountry box="[779,898,1425,1451]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">TAIWAN</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="8.[317,1270,1495,1592]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
1(4) Ocular sulcus rather complex, deeply sinuate inwardly (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1131,1495,1521]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
); eyes more oblique and narrowly spindle-shaped; pronotum with punctation subcontiguous; elytra with rows of separated punctures, not striate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[317,1270,1619,1750]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
2(3) Whole dorsal surface opaque; head and pronotum less closely punctate; elytra with rows of widely spaced foveolate punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1080,1654,1680]" captionStart="Figs 2–6" captionStartId="3.[317,360,1745,1766]" captionTargetBox="[324,1263,575,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2–6. Habitus of Paramisolampidius species: 2 = P. csorbai sp. n., 3 = P. formosanus MASUMOTO, 1981, 4 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 5 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 6 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731872/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[1181,1264,1654,1680]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
; Tehuashe (
<elevation box="[505,658,1689,1715]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="600.0">
<quantity box="[505,581,1689,1715]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
a. s. l.
</elevation>
), 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D7E342FF8DFFE0C4ABFA81FB61FA83:8EA1048FFF8DFFE1C7DBF976FC80F963" box="[682,791,1689,1715]" country="Taiwan" name="Riyuetan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" stateProvince="Nantou">Riyuetan</location>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[803,967,1689,1715]" country="Taiwan" name="Nantou" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Nantou Hsien</collectingRegion>
, C 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1094,1689,1715]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="MASUMOTO, 1981 a" authorityName="MASUMOTO" authorityYear="1981" box="[858,1270,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[858,1027,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">P. formosanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MASUMOTO, K." box="[1035,1270,1724,1750]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="15 - 52" refId="ref4571" refString="MASUMOTO, K. (1981 a) Tenebrionidae of Formosa (2). Elytra 9 (1): 15 - 52." type="journal article" year="1981">
MASUMOTO, 1981 
<emphasis box="[1255,1270,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">a</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1270,439,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
3(2) Head and pronotum opaque, scutellum and elytra shining, alutaceous; head and pronotum closely and coarsely punctate; elytra with rows of narrowly separated punctures (
<figureCitation box="[625,698,510,536]" captionStart="Figs 2–6" captionStartId="3.[317,360,1745,1766]" captionTargetBox="[324,1263,575,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2–6. Habitus of Paramisolampidius species: 2 = P. csorbai sp. n., 3 = P. formosanus MASUMOTO, 1981, 4 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 5 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 6 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731872/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity box="[800,908,510,536]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
; Suleng (
<quantity box="[1016,1114,510,536]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="1100.0">1,100 m</quantity>
a. s. l.), 
<collectingRegion country="Taiwan" name="Taoyuan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taoyuan Hsien</collectingRegion>
, N 
<collectingCountry box="[554,642,545,571]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="MASUMOTO, 1984" authorityName="MASUMOTO" authorityYear="1984" box="[895,1270,545,571]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinugasai">
<emphasis box="[895,1042,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. kinugasai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MASUMOTO, K." box="[1049,1270,545,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="16 - 24" refId="ref4621" refString="MASUMOTO, K. (1984) Tenebrionidae of Formosa (6). Elytra 11 (1 - 2): 16 - 24." type="journal article" year="1984">MASUMOTO, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1270,598,729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
4(1) Ocular sulcus simple, not deeply sinuate (
<figureCitation box="[861,978,598,624]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 7, 10</figureCitation>
) or slightly bulged (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MASUMOTO" authorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenghsiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. tenghsiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation box="[534,616,633,659]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); eyes more transverse and rounded; pronotal punctation either very fine or coarse but punctures clearly separated; elytra striate-punctate, at least in first two rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1269,756,888]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
5(6) Ocular sulcus narrow and incomplete, running from behind to middle of inner margin of eye (
<figureCitation box="[570,646,791,817]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); body slender; pronotum remarkably sparsely and finely punctate; length 
<quantity box="[647,732,827,853]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
; Hohuanshan (
<quantity box="[905,1002,827,853]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="3100.0">3,100 m</quantity>
a. s. l.), 
<collectingRegion box="[1101,1265,827,853]" country="Taiwan" name="Nantou" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Nantou Hsien</collectingRegion>
, C 
<collectingCountry box="[404,492,862,888]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="Merkl &amp; Masumoto, 2008" authorityName="Merkl &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2008" box="[1076,1199,861,887]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="csorbai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1199,861,887]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. csorbai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1207,1269,862,888]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1269,915,976]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">6(5) Ocular sulcus broader and complete (running around whole eye); body more robust; pronotum coarsely punctate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1270,1003,1170]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
7(8) Ocular sulcus simple (
<figureCitation box="[637,723,1003,1029]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); punctures on pronotum mostly rounded; posterior half of prothoracic epipleuron with contiguous punctures forming wrinkles; elytra with strial punctures finer, not wider than width of striae; length 
<quantity box="[378,507,1108,1134]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="13.0">13–16 mm</quantity>
; various localities of C and N 
<collectingCountry box="[863,951,1108,1134]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1270,1003,1170]" box="[887,1269,1143,1170]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authority="(M. T. CHUJO, 1967)" baseAuthorityName="M. T. CHUJO" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[887,1269,1143,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shirozui">
<emphasis box="[887,1014,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. shirozui</emphasis>
(M. T. 
<bibRefCitation author="CHUJO, M. T." box="[1104,1261,1143,1169]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="375 - 381" refId="ref4468" refString="CHUJO, M. T. (1967) A check list of Formosan Tenebrionidae (Coleoptera), 1. Kontyu 35 (4): 375 - 381." type="journal article" year="1967">CHÛJÔ, 1967</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[317,1270,1196,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
8(7) Ocular sulcus slightly bulged inwardly (
<figureCitation box="[841,925,1196,1222]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1737,1758]" captionTargetBox="[354,1233,427,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[352,1235,424,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 7–11. Head of Paramisolampidius species: 7 = P. csorbai sp. n., 8 = P. formosanus MASU- MOTO, 1981, 9 = P. kinugasai MASUMOTO, 1984, 10 = P. shirozui (M. T. CHÛJÔ, 1967), 11 = P. tenghsiensis MASUMOTO, 1984" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731874/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); punctures on pronotum longitudinally ovate; posterior half of prothoracic epipleuron with separate punctures; elytra with strial punctures coarse, distinctly wider than width of striae; length 
<quantity box="[541,717,1302,1328]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="15.5" valueMin="12.5">12.5–15.5 mm</quantity>
; Tenghsi and Liukuei (about 
<quantity box="[1072,1170,1302,1328]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="1400.0">1,400 m</quantity>
a. s. l.), 
<collectingRegion box="[378,505,1337,1363]" country="Taiwan" name="Kaohsiung" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Kaohsiung</collectingRegion>
Hsien, S 
<collectingCountry box="[619,707,1337,1363]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="MASUMOTO, 1984" authorityName="MASUMOTO" authorityYear="1984" box="[866,1270,1337,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenghsiensis">
<emphasis box="[866,1041,1337,1363]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. tenghsiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MASUMOTO, K." box="[1049,1270,1337,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="16 - 24" refId="ref4621" refString="MASUMOTO, K. (1984) Tenebrionidae of Formosa (6). Elytra 11 (1 - 2): 16 - 24." type="journal article" year="1984">MASUMOTO, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
